President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. spoke with President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine and discussed various issues. President Biden highlighted the efforts of the United States, its Allies, partners, and private industry in increasing the costs on Russia for its aggression in Ukraine. He specifically mentioned the decision by Visa and Mastercard to suspend service in Russia, which he welcomed. President Biden mentioned that his administration is providing increased security, humanitarian, and economic assistance to Ukraine and is working with Congress to secure additional funding. He expressed concern about the recent Russian attack on a Ukrainian nuclear power plant and praised the Ukrainian operators for their skill and bravery in keeping the reactors safe. The leaders also discussed the recent talks between Russia and Ukraine.